>-get the seal warm

No SUN ? Try the microwave oven for this one.

>-silicone spray on the seal

Roofing tar provides an assembly lubricant and a perpetual sealing material.
Brush into the glass / rubber channel as well as the metal window frame.
It cleans up with mineral spirits or kerosene. It's also cheap. And a popular
favorite over on the vintagebus list .

>as far as 'wire', actually i used some speaker wire split in half. i dont
>know the guage but its not that thick. i used the same type of wire for the
>other seals i installed a few years ago on a 73 super beetle & it worked
>pefectly.

speaker wire won't take much torque. Use weedwhacker nylon line.

